# 12. Final Short Definition 📚

> DOM (Document Object Model) is a tree-like structure created by the browser that allows JavaScript to access and manipulate HTML and CSS elements dynamically.























| Type          | Purpose               |
| ------------- | --------------------- |
| Document DOM  | Access entire webpage |
| Element DOM   | Access HTML elements  |
