# 1. Document DOM 📄

## Definition

Document DOM represents the entire HTML document.

It is the root object of the webpage.

---

## Uses ✅

* Access webpage content
* Find HTML elements
* Change webpage dynamically

---

## Example 💻

```html id="4ex65u"
<h1 id="title">Hello</h1>
```

```javascript id="rv7tjm"
document.getElementById("title").innerHTML = "Welcome";
```

---

## Real-Time Example 🌍

Changing website title dynamically.

Example:

* YouTube changing page title
* Gmail updating notification count

---

# 2. Element DOM 🏷️

## Definition

Element DOM is used to access and manipulate specific HTML elements.

---

## Uses ✅

* Change text
* Modify CSS
* Add/remove elements

---

## Example 💻

```html id="qg5d4m"
<p id="demo">Original Text</p>
```

```javascript id="ufk0zc"
let para = document.getElementById("demo");
para.style.color = "red";
```

---

## Real-Time Example 🌍

* Changing button color
* Updating form data
* Showing notifications

---

# 3. Attribute DOM ⚙️

## Definition

Attribute DOM is used to access or modify HTML attributes.

Examples of attributes:

* id
* class
* src
* href

---

## Uses ✅

* Change image source
* Update links
* Modify classes

---

## Example 💻

```html id="c3xy26"
<img id="img" src="old.jpg">
```

```javascript id="3m6kfc"
document.getElementById("img").src = "new.jpg";
```

---

## Real-Time Example 🌍

* Profile picture update
* Theme switching
* Dynamic links

---

# 4. Event DOM 🖱️

## Definition

Event DOM handles user interactions/events.

Examples:

* click
* mouseover
* keypress
* submit

---

## Uses ✅

* Button click actions
* Form validation
* Interactive webpages

---

## Example 💻

```html id="mf0v3u"
<button onclick="show()">Click</button>
```

```javascript id="7ob10n"
function show() {
   alert("Button Clicked");
}
```

---

## Real-Time Example 🌍

* Login form submit
* Like button
* Search bar interaction

---

